Package CommonLib.common

'common' package contains interfaces and classes that do not stand alone and can be used in any project.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IStartable
    IStartable: Describes a class that performs a long (can be cyclically) operation that continues until it stops, this class can start and stop an unlimited number of times.
    ScheduledExecutor.IScheduledExecutionHandler<TData>
    ScheduledExecutionHandler: The handler of the scheduled task result.
    UncaughetExceptions.UncaughtExceptionsHandler
    UncaughetExceptionHandler: Describes a handler of uncaught exceptions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlertBuilder
    AlertBuilder: A builder of Alert window.
    ScheduledExecutor
    ScheduledExecutor: A class that execute schedule tasks in fixed rate with result, the class implement IStartable interface.
    Startable
    Startable: Base abstract implementation to IStartable interface.
    UncaughetExceptions
    UncaughetExceptions: A class that refers to exceptions that were not caught.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NotRunningException
    NotRunningException: Unchecked exception which thrown when a IStartable that is not in the 'Running' state is used.

Package CommonLib.common Description

'common' package contains interfaces and classes that do not stand alone and can be used in any project.

'Common' project contains interfaces and classes which are shared both to the server and to the client.
